             shuffling something under her apron; I afterwards served her the print; then I accused them of it.</p>
               <p>Mr. Alley. Q. After you had taken the money for the goods, you accused them of it? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. What money did they lay out with you? - A. Four shillings and sixpence; she said it was for a child's frock. (The property produced and identified by Meredith.</p>
               <p>The prisoners left their defence to their Counsel.</p>
